  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study is designed to examine the effect of benzydamine hydrochloride to postoperative
      sore throat in pediatric patients. We will spray benzydmaine hydrochloride or normal saline
      at oral cavity and the tip of endotracheal tube, than compare the prevalence of postoperative
      sore throat using smartphone application in pediatric patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      1. postoperative sore throat incidence (over 2) 1; no, 2;mild, 3;moderate, 4;severe

        2. scoring of pain with smartphone application (kids pain scale)

        3. incidence of use of rescue pain killer
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
